body:
input

```js
import utils from './lib/utils';
console.log(utils);
```

errors with `Missing file extension for "./lib/utils"  import/extensions`

When set the file extension

```js
import utils from './lib/utils.js';
console.log(utils);
```
errors with `Unexpected use of file extension "js" for "./lib/utils.js"  import/extensions`

As seen on the following issue we can't always expect an array to be destructured.
https://github.com/eslint/eslint/issues/9386

```js
    'prefer-destructuring': ['error', {
      AssignmentExpression: {
        array: false
      },
    }, {
      enforceForRenamedProperties: false,
    }],
```
